title: For Sale:  Beretta PX4 Storm Compact 9mm
postcontent: The Beretta PX4 Storm Compact is a great, yet often overlooked, option for those who want a lightweight, Glock 19 sized pistol but prefer a hammer fired, traditional double action/single action system over a striker configuration. An interesting design aspect of the PX4 is that unlike most pistols on the market, the barrel does not tilt down to unlock from the slide, but rotates instead. Due to the magic of physics and conservation of momentum, recoil forces are dispersed radially, in part, reducing the amount of felt recoil to the shooter. Combined with the mechanical disadvantage prior to slide travel created by the hammer, the PX4 is a surprisingly soft shooting pistol. Comes with two magazines, interchangeable backstraps, and cleaning brushes. title: For Sale:  German Radom VIS model mod.35
postcontent: This is a type II Polish Radom VIS model mod.35 pat. nr. 15567 with German markings on left side of slide and frame.  It has all 3 levers but no stock slot.  Very low serial number, it starts with F and is a four digit serial number, the first number is 6.It must be rare because I can't find information about the F that starts the serial numbers.  Black checkered plastic grips, on left side of grip the letters FB, on the right side of the grip it has three letters VIS.  Germany defeated Poland in 1939 and captured the Radom factory and turned its capabilities toward supplying arms for the Nazi war machine.  I think it was made in Poland in 1942.  Later guns dispensed with the take-down latch.  Earlier guns were slotted for a shorter stock.  VIS on the right grip panel is Latin for "power" or force.  The "FB" on left grip panel stands for Fabryka Brony (weapon factory).The Nazi eagle stampings are on the slide and frame of the left side and there are other markings and letters on the gun as well.  I shot it once, at 20 yds. a 3" group.  Riflings are good, very little darkness in grooves, no pitting.  Finish on gun might be 75%-80%, don't really know how to judge it.Everything on the gun is original and tight.  No pitting, finish is a little worn on left side from holster wear it looks like.  Grips are in excellent condition, magazine is original, gun is very clean.In my opinion, this is the best hand gun that came out of WW11.  They originally made these pistols for the Polish calvary.  These are the last calvary pistols to be made.  I would suggest that you research this hand gun online to find out more about it.  This gun is a bring back or souvenier from WW11, there are no import marks on it.It's an all matching numers gun,  barrel, slide and frame.  Serial numbers are in the mid 6000 range.Price is firm and no trades accepted.For serious and advanced collectors only.Local sale only, I will not mail it out.

title: For Sale:  Daniel Defense DDM4 V5LW AR15 DDM4V5 LW M4 RIFLE
postcontent: Description / Manufacturer Information: The Daniel Defense M4 Carbine V5 is a semi-automatic tactical rifle chambered in 5.56 NATO. The LW has identical features to the V5 and costs the same too, but the difference is the LW has a lightweight barrel, which cuts a third of a pound. The LW uses the Omega X Rail 12 handguards. These handguards are free-floating, so when the barrel heats up and swells they won’t press against each other. It has Picatinny rails running along the top, bottom and sides, which allow for easy mounting of optics or accessories. The top runs continuously and meets with the upper receiver and extends slightly after the front sight. But it is available with fixed sight, flip sights or not sights. It has a mid-length gas operating system, so propellant gases are caught in a tube near the muzzle, the tube guides it back to the bolt and then catches in another tube on the bolt. When the gas is caught, it drives the bolt back. This delays recoil until the projectile has left the bore. Mid-length means that the gas is caught after a medium distance in the barrel, so less pressure is used to push the bolt back (compared to the short-length gas system). Features include a chrome lined bore, a vertical fore-grip, a MagPul buttstock that’s lightweight and adjustable, a cold hammer forged barrel, so a machine carefully carved the grooves in the bore. This process produces accurate and durable rifling. And it has a sling swivel attachment points, so users can attach a combat sling, which allows them to sling it while carrying it at the ready. Daniel Defense recommends the LW for military, law enforcement or personal security. Manufacturer: Daniel Defense Model: 02-123-16029-047 DDM4V5LW Condition: New Caliber/Gauge: 5.56 NATO
